@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Brikon" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on an empty tile (a tile with a small square) and then
click on a neighbouring empty tile, that second tile must be immediately
next (either vertically or horizontally) to the previous clicked tile. If
the tiles are next to each other, a 'brick' will appear there, 'joining'
the two tiles together. Note that you can only click on the empty tiles,
as clicking on part of a brick will have no effect.

  Never isolate single tiles!

  Continue the game until all 32 bricks are placed, then the game will
check if there are continuous straight lines from one edge to the other,
if there are any, Brikon will show them in colour as well as show how
many there are, and then it will clear the board and start a new game.

  You can choose the number of 'starting' bricks by clicking on any part
of the 'slider gadget' bar located under the game board. Clicking on
either side of the slider will either increase or decrease the number of
starting bricks.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}Replay@{ub} button.

  Oh, one more thing: do NOT isolate single tiles!

  Have fun!

